# This file is used by "git commit" to auto-populate the commit message template:
#   git config commit.template .gitmessage
#   git commit --template=.gitmessage

# === Summary (required) ===
# Format: <type>: <short imperative summary>
# Short imperative sentence, max 50 characters.
# Do not end the subject line with a period.
# Separate subject from body with a blank line.
#
# Common types:
#   feat: add a user-facing capability
#   fix: correct a bug
#   docs: update documentation only
#   chore: maintain repository metadata or tooling
#   refactor: restructure code without behavior changes
#   test: add or update tests
#
# Examples:
#   fix: handle empty configuration
#   feat: add user deletion endpoint
#   docs: update repository inventory

<summary>

# === Description (optional but recommended) ===
# Describe the context, rationale, and solution.
# Explain what changed and why. Avoid implementation details unless useful.
# Max 72 characters per line.
#
# Example:
#   The previous loader crashed when the config file was empty.
#   Added guard clauses and default values to ensure stability.

<description>

# === Impact (optional) ===
# Mention side effects, compatibility issues, migrations, etc.
# Max 72 characters per line.
#
# Examples:
#   No breaking change
#   Requires migration 20251126-add-index.sql

<impact>

# === References (optional) ===
# Link to related issues, tickets, or documents.
# Max 72 characters per line.
#
# Examples:
#   Refs: PROJ-1289
#   Fixes: #42

<references>

# === Notes for reviewers (optional) ===
# Anything useful for code review or testing context.
# Max 72 characters per line.

<review notes>
